nban for maintenance work to enhance customer value delivery.", "competency_name": "Customer / Value Orientation"}, "6": {"level": 6, "source": "template", "customized": false, "level_name": "Mastering SE", "gap_percentage": 100.0, "objective_text": "Participants can set guidelines for models and write guidelines for good modeling.", "competency_name": "Systems Modelling and Analysis"}, "7": {"level": 6, "source": "pmt_customized", "customized": true, "level_name": "Mastering SE", "gap_percentage": 100.0, "objective_text": "Participants are able to manage their relationships with colleagues and superiors in a sustainable manner within the context of Scrum and Kanban processes. They can resolve conflicts, bring different perspectives together, and negotiate sustainable compromises while utilizing tools such as Microsoft Project Server for task management and collaborative platforms for effective communication.", "competency_name": "Communication"}, "11": {"level": 6, "source": "pmt_customized", "customized": true, "level_name": "Mastering SE", "gap_percentage": 100.0, "objective_text": "Participants can evaluate decisions and establish overarching decision-making processes within the context of Scrum and Kanban methodologies. They can introduce decision methods company-wide, utilizing tools like Microsoft Project Server for project management and IBM DOORS for requirements management, and set up the decision management toolchain to enhance collaboration and efficiency in development and support work.", "competency_name": "Decision Management"}, "12": {"level": 6, "source": "pmt_customized", "customized": true, "level_name": "Mastering SE", "gap_percentage": 100.0, "objective_text": "The participant can define a comprehensive information management process tailored to the implementation of Scrum and Kanban methodologies, establish documentation methods and standards using tools like IBM DOORS and Jama Connect, and set up the information management toolchain incorporating platforms for project management, collaboration, and CI/CD workflows within the organization.", "competency_name": "Information Management"}, "13": {"level": 6, "source": "pmt_customized", "customized": true, "level_name": "Mastering SE", "gap_percentage": 100.0, "objective_text": "The participant is able to recognize all relevant configuration items and build a complete configuration across all items within the context of Scrum and Kanban processes. They can identify improvements, propose solutions, support others, and set up the relevant tool landscape, including tools like IBM DOORS, Jama Connect, and the source control platform for version control.", "competency_name": "Configuration Management"}, "14": {"level": 6, "source": "pmt_customized", "customized": true, "level_name": "Mastering SE", "gap_percentage": 100.0, "objective_text": "Participants are able to recognize shortcomings in the requirements definition process within the context of Scrum and Kanban methodologies and develop suggestions for improvement. They can guide colleagues in requirements formulation using tools such as IBM DOORS and Jama Connect, and introduce estimation techniques like Planning Poker to enhance the requirements management process in the enterprise.", "competency_name": "Requirements Definition"}, "15": {"level": 6, "source": "template", "customized": false, "level_name": "Mastering SE", "gap_percentage": 100.0, "objective_text": "Participants can recognize shortcomings in the process and develop suggestions for improvement. They can create and manage high-complexity models and set up the toolchain for system modeling.", "competency_name": "System Architecting"}, "16": {"level": 6, "source": "pmt_customized", "customized": true, "level_name": "Mastering SE", "gap_percentage": 100.0, "objective_text": "The participant is able to set up a test strategy and test plans at an early stage, conduct design reviews, and establish verification and validation processes using tools such