4	34	ISO 26262 for automotive safety, V-model development process, ASPICE compliance	Agile with 2-week sprints, Scrum framework, Requirements traceability, Trade-off analysis	DOORS for requirements management, JIRA for project tracking, Enterprise Architect for SysML modeling, Confluence for documentation	Automotive embedded systems and ADAS development	Focus on safety-critical systems for autonomous driving applications. Team works on sensor fusion and decision-making algorithms.	2025-11-07 00:42:30.9005	2025-11-07 00:42:30.9005
5	38	Systems Engineering V-model, ISO 15288 lifecycle processes, Requirements engineering per ISO 29148	Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE), Requirements-driven design, System integration testing	SysML tools (Cameo Systems Modeler), Requirements management (Polarion), Configuration management (Git)	Aerospace and defense systems	Focus on complex system integration for avionics and flight control systems. Heavy emphasis on verification and validation.	2025-11-07 00:42:30.908605	2025-11-07 00:42:30.908605
7	48	The document describes several processes including a regulatory compliance framework, design control process, risk management process, document control, and supplier management.\n\nStakeholder Analysis identifies and categorizes stakeholders; Engineering Change Proposal (ECP) process manages changes; Configuration Control Board (CCB) operation oversees configuration management; Test and Evaluation Master Plan (TEMP) outlines test activities.\n\nThe team operates without formal processes, relying on communication and collaboration to build the product, with weekly syncs on Mondays.	The methods identified include FMEA for hazard identification, risk-benefit analysis, software requirements analysis, and usability testing.\n\nStakeholder Analysis categorizes stakeholders; Requirements Elicitation Techniques gather requirements; Functional Decomposition breaks down functions; Trade Study Process evaluates architectures; Worst-case Analysis assesses performance; Monte Carlo Simulation evaluates uncertainty; Risk Assessment scores risks.	Tools mentioned include an FMEA spreadsheet for risk management and MasterControl QMS for document control.\n\nPugh Matrix is used for assessing candidate architectures.\n\nTools used include VS Code for coding, GitHub for version control, Notion for project management, Figma for design, and Slack for communication.	\N	\N	2025-12-04 22:03:41.675231	2025-12-04 22:12:43.904498
8	53	Implementation of Scrum with defined ceremonies, roles, and artifacts to manage the development process. Utilization of Kanban for maintenance and support work with defined board columns and policies. Use of Planning Poker and Velocity Tracking for estimating story points and planning sprints. Adoption of Pair Programming, Code Review, Test-Driven Development (TDD), and Continuous Integration to enhance code quality and collaboration.	A consensus-based estimation technique using the Fibonacci sequence for story point estimation. A software development approach where tests are written before code to ensure functionality.	The document lists various tools for requirements management, modeling and simulation, project management, configuration management, testing, and collaboration, including IBM DOORS, Jama Connect, IBM Rhapsody, MATLAB/Simulink, Microsoft Project Server, and others.\n\nA project management tool used for Scrum and Kanban boards to track progress and manage tasks. A documentation tool used to create and share project-related documents. A communication tool used for team channels and standup meetings. A video conferencing tool used for remote ceremonies. A collaborative online whiteboard platform used for remote retrospectives and planning. A source control platform used for version control of code. A CI/CD tool used for automating workflows in GitHub. An integrated development environment (IDE) used for coding.	\N	\N	2026-01-06 01:33:06.013191	2026-01-06 01:33:06.013191
6	29	The document describes the V-Model development lifecycle, standards compliance requirements, structured review gates, and the Change Control Board process for managing requirement changes.\n\nModel reviews shall check completeness of traceability links, consistency between diagrams, adherence to naming conventions, proper use of stereotypes, and model simulation results where applicable.	No specific methods were identified in the document.\n\nThe document describes various SysML diagrams including Requirements Diagram (REQ), Block Definition Diagram (BDD), Internal Block Diagram (IBD), Activity Diagram (ACT), State Machine Diagram (STM), and best practices for modeling.	No specific tools were identified in the document.\n\nThe document lists various tools including IBM DOORS Next Generation for requirements management, Jama Connect for collaboration, IBM Rhapsody for modeling, MATLAB/Simulink for simulation, Microsoft Project Server for project management, Jira Software for agile management, Git for version control, and several others for testing and collaboration.			2025-11-08 05:21:58.090439	2025-11-28 15:09:39.439278
